{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"72d016f6-b25f-4533-a3b8-31bc8da52a44","content":"The official MCP Registry is the **[mcp-registry](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry)** repo on GitHub. To register your server:\n\n1. **Fork** `https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry`\n2. **Add a JSON file** under `servers/` named after your package (e.g., `servers/my-mcp-server.json`) following the registry's schema — typically including:\n   - `name`, `description`, `vendor`\n   - `sourceUrl` (your GitHub repo)\n   - `distribution` with a `nuget` entry pointing to your package\n3. **Open a Pull Request** against the `main` branch.\n4. The maintainers will review and merge it.\n\nCheck the repo's **README** and existing entries in `servers/` for the exact schema and required fields:\n\n```\nhttps://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry\n```\n\n> **Tip:** Make sure your NuGet package metadata (description, tags, project URL) is complete — reviewers often check that the package page looks good before merging.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"faa5d6a8-a627-4352-a020-da3fff518078","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know about this process.\n\nLet me check if there's any relevant information in the current working directory or if this relates to the repository context.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"C03B:6467:1D1549C:20AB89B:6A07C206"},"id":"6a4989c2-0ea0-4f82-949b-80521c34b871","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:02:07.861Z","parentId":"8f788ce4-a1fd-46cd-9060-da1bc5a8f424"}
